OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779311467
OL,3,CEbola cases pass 600 but global risk
OL,4,Cremains low, says WHO
OL,6,FThe first person died from the virus
OL,7,Fon April 24 in Bunia, but the
OL,8,Fconfirmation did not come for weeks,
OL,9,Fand the body was repatriated to the
OL,10,FMongbwalu health zone, a mining area
OL,11,Fwith a large population.
OL,13,FThe type of Ebola, Bundibugyo, also
OL,14,Fhas no approved medicines or vaccines
OL,15,Favailable.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
